  "definitions": [
    {
      "definition": "A usually aggressive malignant neoplasm arising from the uterine corpus and less often the cervix.  It is characterized by the presence of two components: a malignant epithelial component and a sarcomatous component.  In the uterine corpus the epithelial component is usually glandular whereas in the cervix is usually non-glandular.  Carcinosarcoma of the cervix, although it is aggressive, it may have a better prognosis compared to the uterine corpus carcinosarcoma.",
      "type": "DEFINITION",
      "source": "NCI"
    }
  ],
